1
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,840
Why is the power out?

2
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,359
We are still investigating the cause.

3
00:01:26,439 --> 00:01:27,920
The whole museum is out.

4
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:29,959
The monitoring system hasn't fully recovered.

5
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,959
The team followed them to the museum.

6
00:01:32,519 --> 00:01:33,879
Squid also entered the museum.

7
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,680
Now we have people watching every entrance.

8
00:01:36,719 --> 00:01:38,400
Don't worry, Squid won't get away.

9
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,120
Thank you.

10
00:01:45,359 --> 00:01:46,480
You go check it out.

11
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:47,200
Okay.

12
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:52,319
Xunxun, thanks to you,

13
00:01:52,519 --> 00:01:53,760
the visitors coming to the exhibition tomorrow

14
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,680
are basically here for

15
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,959
these star artifacts.

16
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,959
You should get some rest, you've worked hard.

17
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:09,840
What's that sound?

18
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,719
Me... the spare work phone.

19
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:30,000
Thanks to you.

20
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:31,599
Get some rest.

21
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,759
Why aren't you leaving?

22
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,039
This senior

23
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:37,520
is obviously into you,

24
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,719
but he's not good enough for you.

25
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:39,719
You deserve better.

26
00:02:39,719 --> 00:02:40,800
You should look elsewhere.

27
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:42,879
Who should I look at?

28
00:02:43,639 --> 00:02:44,280
You.

29
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,039
Hmm?

30
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:48,680
I'm your family's carefully selected match.

31
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,240
What's wrong? Am I not good enough?

32
00:02:50,639 --> 00:02:52,400
Sometimes, the dating market

33
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,280
has its share of mismatched pairs.

34
00:02:57,639 --> 00:02:58,439
How about this?

35
00:02:59,439 --> 00:03:01,080
Let's go on a proper date.

36
00:03:01,319 --> 00:03:02,639
Show me around your museum,

37
00:03:02,639 --> 00:03:04,240
and check me out. What do you say?

38
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,639
Sorry.

39
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:15,879
Let's go.

40
00:03:16,599 --> 00:03:17,680
You said you wanted to check me out,

41
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,960
but why are we in such a remote place?

42
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:51,360
Do you know how many people have been following me?

43
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,240
Thank goodness you found this tunnel.

44
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,560
Mr. Ke,

45
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:56,919
how did you find this place?

46
00:03:57,759 --> 00:03:59,080
I work here.

47
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:00,680
It's easy for me to find this place.

48
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,680
How about the thing I want?

49
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,360
I've got it.

50
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,360
According to your plan,

51
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,879
I had the USB chip put into this jade disc.

52
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:16,360
It was made by a master craftsman.

53
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:19,279
It's a perfect replica.

54
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,920
Is this the real one you want?

55
00:04:26,879 --> 00:04:27,680
Mr. Ke,

56
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,480
I know its value.

57
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:33,319
If you only offer this price

58
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,920
after causing such a big trouble,

59
00:04:35,439 --> 00:04:39,079
I'm afraid I have to find another buyer.

60
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,199
Octopus hasn't shown up yet.

61
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,600
He must still be in the gallery.

62
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,120
But we can't see the surveillance.

63
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,720
Our people are still looking for him.

64
00:05:14,319 --> 00:05:15,319
It's pretty.

65
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:20,040
If you mind, I'll delete it.

66
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:23,160
Young Master Shen, taking photos without permission is not good.

67
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:25,040
But it's not shameful

68
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,079
to have a crush on me.

69
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,759
Right?

70
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:30,079
Then I'll set it as my screensaver.

71
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:34,959
Master, if you keep this pace of awkward chatting,

72
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:35,839
you won't fall in love.

73
00:05:35,839 --> 00:05:37,360
The girl will give birth to a baby with someone else.

74
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,879
Use your trump card.

75
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,279
There is no octopus.

76
00:05:41,839 --> 00:05:42,800
What?

77
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,240
You want to see fish?

78
00:05:44,839 --> 00:05:45,680
I said

79
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:46,519
jade.

80
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:47,720
I want to see jade.

81
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,240
The jade exhibition is tomorrow.

82
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,560
Come back tomorrow.

83
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,279
[Find a chance to hold hands.]

84
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,360
[Ask her to take you inside now.]

85
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,360
Wait a minute.

86
00:05:58,839 --> 00:05:59,879
Since we're here,

87
00:06:00,519 --> 00:06:01,639
is there no

88
00:06:01,639 --> 00:06:03,040
companion ticket or something?

89
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:05,439
Since when are you my companion?

90
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,759
Just now.

91
00:06:07,439 --> 00:06:09,120
The man who gave you flowers

92
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,959
will become your companion.

93
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,519
I feel like

94
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:15,160
you're not telling the truth.

95
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,079
That won't work.

96
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:19,319
We can't say it's for Xue Li.

97
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:26,040
Actually,

98
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,160
I like you.

99
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,839
Actually, I want to pursue you.

100
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,560
From the first time

101
00:06:38,199 --> 00:06:39,560
we went on a blind date,

102
00:06:39,959 --> 00:06:41,319
I wanted to tell you.

103
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:48,720
I know your feelings.

104
00:06:49,319 --> 00:06:51,079
But what I want to say is

105
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,639
the jade pendant on your chest

106
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,240
is a pair.

107
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,560
What?

108
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,439
If I'm not mistaken,

109
00:07:16,639 --> 00:07:20,759
The pendant came from the stone's yin side.

110
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:23,279
So there's a yang side?

111
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:28,319
These two jade pendants

112
00:07:28,319 --> 00:07:30,199
were made by my great-grandfather Jiang Chihui.

113
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,079
Your great-grandfather Jiang Chihui?

114
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,560
You're the descendant of the Jiang family?

115
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:39,399
Why haven't you mentioned it before?

116
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:42,680
There was a conflict between them.

117
00:07:43,319 --> 00:07:44,319
Family secrets

118
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,560
are not for outsiders.

119
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,120
But

120
00:07:47,399 --> 00:07:49,560
you look a bit like

121
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,279
my great-grandfather.

122
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:53,800
You're like his

123
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,519
look-alike.

124
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,680
So I've always been

125
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,319
interested in your jade pendant.

126
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,800
I see.

127
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,800
A dragon and a phoenix.

128
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:09,439
[At first,]

129
00:08:10,199 --> 00:08:11,839
[you went to auction for the jade]

130
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:13,560
[and had your eye on this pendant]

131
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,879
[to restore them.]

132
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,800
The family tickets are sold out.

133
00:08:21,879 --> 00:08:24,079
But I won't let you leave disappointed.

134
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:26,560
Let's go to the exhibition hall and see.

135
00:08:31,399 --> 00:08:33,799
[I need to put the real jade back before power is restored.]

136
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:35,759
[Otherwise, Jiang Xun will find out]

137
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,320
[and ruin the plan.]

138
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,960
This is the old house of our great-grandparents.

139
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:41,799
Now it's a museum.

140
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,960
The environment is really nice.

141
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,240
It has almost retained

142
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,639
80% of the original architecture.

143
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:52,600
Where do you usually exhibit your jades?

144
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,919
Over there.

145
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:54,960
Let me show you.

146
00:09:14,519 --> 00:09:15,320
[Senior,]

147
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,639
[on one hand,]

148
00:09:47,639 --> 00:09:49,200
[Shen Shutu is relentlessly pursuing you,]

149
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,879
[On the other hand,]

150
00:09:50,879 --> 00:09:52,399
[Ke Yu'ang's considerate care.]

151
00:09:52,639 --> 00:09:54,679
[This secret battle is about to escalate.]

152
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,679
[In reality, foreign spies]

153
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:59,120
[often use online dating as a cover,]

154
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,519
[carefully disguising their identities,]

155
00:10:00,519 --> 00:10:02,000
[creating fated encounters,]

156
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,679
[weaving sweet traps,]

157
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:06,440
[attempting to recruit and subvert our confidential personnel,]

158
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,559
[and steal state secrets.]

159
00:10:07,919 --> 00:10:09,679
[The online world is complex and chaotic.]

160
00:10:09,679 --> 00:10:11,039
[Facing unexpected romantic opportunities,]

161
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:12,879
[it is imperative to remain vigilant.]
